        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> having semi recently aquired /pet hold id like to add some observations on how this affects pulling/xping and about the skill in general</P><P>1st, on the skill its self, its great, i dont regret it in the least<BR>some would dispute its value post the pet changes but to me, its invaluable, dont need to hvae my fanger on a /pet bakc off hotkey while pulling casters, dont need to worry bout a pet eatting rage when im getting hit(normally round the last tick or 2 of splurt comes rage)and other assorted uses</P><P>my only beef wtih the skill is how often you need to /pet hold<BR>it is not a passive command(like /pet taunt on/off), after a mob dies, you need to /pet hold, when moving a pet and /pet guard here, you need to /pet hold, i end up spamming this hotkey <BR>also, as noted on other posts /pet hold does not clear the hate list(like /pet back off), so after /pet hold, your pet will still go after what it wants after its told to attack(this can be bad when pulling, with the mez changes its not a terror CC wise)<BR>an easy fix would be to tag a hate list clearing onto /pet hold, but my preference were to be if it were made a passive command, summon a pet, /pet guard here(or me depending on what your oding) then /pet taunt off/on, /pet hold on/off, that why, i can send a pet in, drop dots, go work on another pull etc... witout hvaing to /pet hold before i go, i should prolly /feedback this idea, </P><P>now, the primary reason i got /pet hold was so i could pull, AND have a pet up, a luxury i could not afford before, in most situations i would pull to get a camp broken well enough, and if more dps was needed, break a pet out and just help out on CC</P><P>/pet hold allows me to really push some nice dps in xp groups(i now have pyre as well so my grouping dps is at least doubled if not tripled)</P><P>i stronly reccomend any necros who enjoy pulling and do so often invest into this skill (btw, DC + LB + /pet hold = Lich title)</P><P></P><P>Kriista Silence<BR>Warlock of Veeshan</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=103458" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=103458</a></font></td>
