        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Something interesting occurred to me the other night when trying to split some goranga scouts in ME. Not sure how many of you have tried this, and I'm not sure it will always work -- haven't had a chance to test it yet. Anyway the strat is as follows:</P><P>Go to location of -2- mobs you want to split, I believe it can't be anymore than 2 or you'll be dealing with more agro than you want... if you cast a no dmg spell on the one you don't want and then run back a little ways and FD, the one you cast on will return to his spawn point while the one didn't cast on will stay on you.</P><P>How I found this out was I was going to try to root split them by rooting one then hightailing it back to grp and FD'ing til root wore off, but root got resisted right off the bat, so instead I ran a little ways and I FD'd and I noticed the one I had cast on walked back to spawn point while the other one kinda corpse camped me. When I stood up, I re-agrod the one that I did not attempt to root, and the one that I attempted to root stayed put.</P><P>Was this just a fluke?</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=107061" target="_blank">57th DE Defiler of Tunare</a></font></td>
