        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'>Blackwinter</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Nice guide. </P><P>Just one note to pulling in HoT: I really prefer not to pull there. Lets face the facts: Monks have at least 1k more HP, way better defense skills, rapid FD (and their FD tends to work) and critical mend. And most mobs warp.</P><P>Necro pulling tends to go like this: I tagged a max lvl ancient guardian wurm at the stairs (i have approx 4050 hp). It warped up (like always) and i got a full round of max melee dmg, a full AoE hit and (of course) a stun. MA cleric and druid start heal spells, i start QVeil, get another full melee round (interrupt, stun) and another AoE. Needless to say that i am dead, because its nearly impossible to get the mob of me at that time and i cant channel a spell. A monk would just use FD, mend, FD. [Actually it would have been better to let the MA tag in this special case.]</P><P></P><P><BR> </font></td>
